Four passengers who allegedly damaged the property of Air Peace at the Murtala Muhammed Airport, Lagos were arraigned before an Ogba Magistratesâ€™ Court in Lagos yesterday. The passengers appeared before Magistrate I.A Abina on a three-count charge of malicious damage. Two out of the four passengers, however evaded the arraignment and are now at large, it was learnt. The two arraigned passengers, Mrs Halima Mohammed and one Mr. Osagie however pleaded not guilty to the three count charge. The Police alleged that the defendants had committed the offences on May 26 at the General Aviation Terminal (GAT) of the Murtala Muhammed Airport. The passengers were accused of damaging a car that belonged to Air Peace and assaulting a pilot while demanding compensation from the airline over the delay of their flight last Friday. The court granted a N100, 000 bail each to the passengers with two sureties in like sum. The magistrate also fixed May 30 for perfection of bail and July 2 for mention.